    <div class="slide">
        <h1>Treatment Options for Breast Cancer</h1>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Surgery:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Lumpectomy</li>
                    <li>Mastectomy</li>
                    <li>Sentinel node biopsy</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Radiation Therapy:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Post-surgery to eliminate residual cancer cells</li>
                    <li>External beam vs. brachytherapy</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Systemic Therapies:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Chemotherapy</li>
                    <li>Hormonal therapy (e.g., Tamoxifen, Aromatase inhibitors)</li>
                    <li>Targeted therapies (e.g., HER2 inhibitors)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Immunotherapy:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>For specific subtypes of breast cancer</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="slide">
        <h2>Additional Considerations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Patient's age and overall health</li>
            <li>Stage and subtype of breast cancer</li>
            <li>Patient preferences and values</li>
            <li>Multidisciplinary approach for optimal care</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

